Advanced Selectors

->        {
                $("div > p").css("border","1px dotted black")
            });

Explanation:
This will be only valid for all the div paragraphs in the file.


->         {
                $("div > p.one").css("border","1px dotted black")
            });

Explanation:
This will valid only for div where paragraph has a class as one.

-> {
                $("#textbox +ul").css("border","1px dotted black")
            });
  Explantion:
  This will be only valid for textbox Selectors and unordered list.

  Try these (refer file10.html)
  ---------------
FILTER Advanced

->
Example:
  {
                $("p:first-child").css("border","1px dotted black")
            });

  Explantion:it will give the properties only for 1st paragraphs.

  ->Example:
          {
                $("p:last-of-type").css("border","1px dotted black")
            });

Explantion:it will exibit  only for the last paragraph.

->
Example:
 $("p:contains('ping-pong')").css("border","1px dotted black")

 Explantion:it will only exhibit for those that contains the specific word given in the brackets.

 ->Example:
  $("p:nth-child(2)").css("border","1px dotted black")

  Explantion:it will only exhibit for the second child of the div.

   
